# Regression fixture for issue #43 (baseline): a species initial condition set
# by a DIRECT primary parameter (R0). R0 appears in NO rate law, so its only
# influence on the trajectory is through the initial condition of R. This is the
# case that already seeded correctly (∂R(0)/∂R0 = 1); it anchors the derived-IC
# counterpart (ic_derived.net) — both must match a rebuild finite difference.
begin parameters
    1 R0   100.0   # Constant
    2 kf   0.5     # Constant
end parameters
begin species
    1 R() R0
    2 P() 0.0
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 2 kf   #_R_decay
end reactions
begin groups
    1 R_tot 1
    2 P_tot 2
end groups
